  "text": "[34] The assay is traceable to the Ghent University 25(OH)vitamin D Reference Measurement Procedure (RMP) and has also achieved certification from the CDC-VDSCP [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . When this study was performed the ADVIA Centaur Vitamin D Total assay was the only assay of the ones tested that was CDC-VDSCP certified. [41] the total CVs were in the range of 12.6-10.8% (19.8-280 .0 nmol/L, 7.9-112.1 ng/mL,) for serum and 9.7-9.5% (45.0-154.5 nmol/L, 18.0-61.8 ng/mL) for kit controls.",
